The paper proposes a technique for processing large datasets in machine learning applications on MapReduce, which is a distributed computing framework commonly used in data-intensive applications. This suggests that the paper may belong to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) category. The paper also focuses on producing fast and accurate approximate results, which is a common goal in machine learning research, indicating that it may belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) category. The proposed technique involves aggregating information from input data, which is a common technique in database research, suggesting that the paper may also belong to the Databases (cs.DB) category. The paper also mentions identifying parts of input data most related to result accuracy, which is a common problem in data science and data mining research, indicating that it may belong to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) category. Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed technique using real machine learning applications and datasets, which suggests that it may also belong to the Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV) category.
